# Phase 5: Tabbed Settings Modal & Keyboard Shortcuts

## Overview
Implement a comprehensive modal system with tab support for settings. Create a settings modal with three tabs: Directories, General Shortcuts, and Scrubbing Configuration. Also implement a separate modal for marker details editing.

## Prerequisites
- Phase 1-4 completed
- Basic keyboard handling established
- Marker system functional

## Tasks

### 1. Base Modal System Architecture
- [ ] Create `BaseModal` view component
- [ ] Implement modal presentation/dismissal
- [ ] Add backdrop with dismiss on click
- [ ] Support ESC key for closing
- [ ] Add animation transitions
- [ ] Ensure proper focus management

**Base Structure:**
```swift
struct BaseModal<Content: View>: View {
    @Binding var isPresented: Bool
    let title: String
    let content: Content

    var body: some View {
        ZStack {
            // Backdrop
            Color.black.opacity(0.3)
                .ignoresSafeArea()
                .onTapGesture { isPresented = false }

            // Modal Container
            VStack(spacing: 0) {
                // Title Bar
                HStack {
                    Text(title)
                        .font(.headline)
                    Spacer()
                    Button("√ó") { isPresented = false }
                }
                .padding()

                // Content
                content
                    .padding()
            }
            .background(Color(NSColor.windowBackgroundColor))
            .cornerRadius(10)
            .shadow(radius: 20)
            .frame(minWidth: 600, minHeight: 400)
        }
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- Modal appears centered
- ESC key closes modal
- Click outside closes modal
- Smooth animations

### 2. Tab System Implementation
- [ ] Create `TabbedView` component
- [ ] Support dynamic tab configuration
- [ ] Implement tab selection state
- [ ] Add keyboard navigation between tabs
- [ ] Style active/inactive tabs
- [ ] Remember last selected tab

**Tab Component:**
```swift
struct TabbedView: View {
    @State private var selectedTab = 0
    let tabs: [(title: String, content: AnyView)]

    var body: some View {
        VStack(spacing: 0) {
            // Tab Bar
            HStack(spacing: 0) {
                ForEach(0..<tabs.count, id: \.self) { index in
                    TabButton(
                        title: tabs[index].title,
                        isSelected: selectedTab == index,
                        action: { selectedTab = index }
                    )
                }
                Spacer()
            }
            .background(Color(NSColor.separatorColor))

            // Tab Content
            tabs[selectedTab].content
                .frame(maxWidth: .infinity, maxHeight: .infinity)
        }
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- Tabs switch smoothly
- Active tab clearly indicated
- Content updates correctly

### 3. Settings Modal - Tab 1: Directories
- [ ] Create directory selection UI
- [ ] Default video directory picker
- [ ] Default metadata directory picker
- [ ] Use `NSOpenPanel` for folder selection
- [ ] Display current selections
- [ ] Save button updates preferences

**Directory Tab UI:**
```swift
struct DirectoriesTab: View {
    @AppStorage("defaultVideoDirectory") var videoDirectory = ""
    @AppStorage("defaultMetadataDirectory") var metadataDirectory = ""

    var body: some View {
        Form {
            // Video Directory
            HStack {
                Text("Default Video Directory:")
                Text(videoDirectory.isEmpty ? "Not Set" : videoDirectory)
                    .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                Spacer()
                Button("Choose...") {
                    selectDirectory(for: \.videoDirectory)
                }
            }

            // Metadata Directory
            HStack {
                Text("Default Metadata Directory:")
                Text(metadataDirectory.isEmpty ? "Not Set" : metadataDirectory)
                    .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                Spacer()
                Button("Choose...") {
                    selectDirectory(for: \.metadataDirectory)
                }
            }
        }
        .padding()
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- Can select directories
- Paths display correctly
- Settings persist

### 4. Settings Modal - Tab 2: General Shortcuts
- [ ] List all non-scrubbing shortcuts
- [ ] Editable shortcut fields
- [ ] Conflict detection
- [ ] Reset to defaults button
- [ ] Group shortcuts by category

**Shortcuts to Include:**
- Play/Pause (Space)
- Add Marker (M)
- Delete Marker (Delete)
- Previous Marker ([)
- Next Marker (])
- Open Settings (Cmd+,)
- Open Marker Details (Enter)
- Save Project (Cmd+S)
- Load Project (Cmd+O)

**Shortcut Editor:**
```swift
struct ShortcutRow: View {
    let name: String
    @Binding var shortcut: KeyboardShortcut

    var body: some View {
        HStack {
            Text(name)
            Spacer()
            ShortcutRecorder(shortcut: $shortcut)
                .frame(width: 120)
        }
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- All shortcuts listed
- Can modify shortcuts
- Conflicts highlighted
- Changes apply immediately

### 5. Settings Modal - Tab 3: Scrubbing Configuration
- [ ] Table view for scrubbing configs
- [ ] Add/remove configuration rows
- [ ] Edit backward/forward keys
- [ ] Number input for seek times
- [ ] Frame count validation
- [ ] Set active configuration

**Scrubbing Table Structure:**
| Name | Backward | Forward | Playing (sec) | Paused (frames) | Active |
|------|----------|---------|---------------|-----------------|--------|
| Default | ‚Üê | ‚Üí | 5.0 | 1 | ‚úì |
| Fine | J | L | 1.0 | 5 | |
| Coarse | Shift+‚Üê | Shift+‚Üí | 30.0 | 30 | |

**Implementation:**
```swift
struct ScrubbingTab: View {
    @State private var configs: [ScrubbingConfig] = []

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            // Table Header
            HStack {
                Text("Name").frame(width: 100)
                Text("Backward").frame(width: 80)
                Text("Forward").frame(width: 80)
                Text("Playing (s)").frame(width: 100)
                Text("Paused (f)").frame(width: 100)
                Text("Active").frame(width: 60)
            }

            // Config Rows
            List(configs) { config in
                ScrubbingConfigRow(config: $configs[config])
            }

            // Add Button
            Button("Add Configuration") {
                configs.append(ScrubbingConfig.default)
            }
        }
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- Can add/remove configs
- Values update properly
- Active config switches
- Validation prevents invalid values

### 6. Marker Details Modal
- [ ] Display marker timestamp (read-only)
- [ ] Editable rating (1-5 stars)
- [ ] Labels text field
- [ ] Frame number display
- [ ] Save/Cancel buttons
- [ ] Delete marker option

**Marker Modal UI:**
```swift
struct MarkerDetailsModal: View {
    @Binding var marker: Marker
    @Binding var isPresented: Bool

    var body: some View {
        BaseModal(isPresented: $isPresented, title: "Marker Details") {
            VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 20) {
                // Timestamp
                HStack {
                    Text("Time:")
                    Text(marker.timestamp.timeString)
                    Text("(Frame \(frameNumber))")
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                }

                // Rating
                HStack {
                    Text("Rating:")
                    StarRating(rating: $marker.rating)
                }

                // Labels
                VStack(alignment: .leading) {
                    Text("Labels:")
                    TextField("Enter labels...", text: $labelsText)
                        .textFieldStyle(RoundedBorderTextFieldStyle())
                }

                // Buttons
                HStack {
                    Button("Delete", role: .destructive) {
                        deleteMarker()
                    }
                    Spacer()
                    Button("Cancel") { isPresented = false }
                    Button("Save") { saveChanges() }
                        .keyboardShortcut(.defaultAction)
                }
            }
            .frame(width: 400)
        }
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- Modal opens on marker selection
- Can edit rating and labels
- Changes save correctly
- Delete removes marker

### 7. Global Keyboard Shortcut System
- [ ] Create central shortcut manager
- [ ] Register all shortcuts
- [ ] Handle shortcut conflicts
- [ ] Support modifier keys
- [ ] Enable/disable shortcuts based on context

**Manager Implementation:**
```swift
class KeyboardShortcutManager: ObservableObject {
    static let shared = KeyboardShortcutManager()

    @Published var shortcuts: [String: KeyboardShortcut] = [:]

    func register(_ action: String, shortcut: KeyboardShortcut) {
        shortcuts[action] = shortcut
    }

    func handleKeyEvent(_ event: NSEvent) -> Bool {
        // Process key event against registered shortcuts
    }
}
```

**User Verification:**
- All shortcuts work globally
- Context-aware activation
- No system shortcut conflicts

## Testing Requirements
